// C3: Physical sensing components
instance BuildingTemperatureSensor : DTDFVocab:SensingComponent [
    base:desc "Sensor configured by Building Control Engineers within BIM environment to monitor environmental temperature in physical building systems. Part of the BIM-enriched device modeling process supporting real-time data collection."
    DTDFVocab:producedData BuildingTemperatureDataTransmitted
]

instance BuildingHumiditySensor : DTDFVocab:SensingComponent [
    base:desc "Sensor configured by Building Control Engineers within BIM environment to monitor relative humidity levels in physical building systems. Part of the BIM-enriched device modeling process supporting real-time data collection."
    DTDFVocab:producedData BuildingHumidityDataTransmitted
]

instance BuildingPressureSensor : DTDFVocab:SensingComponent [
    base:desc "Sensor configured by Building Control Engineers within BIM environment to monitor pressure conditions in building systems (e.g., HVAC, plumbing). Part of the BIM-enriched device modeling process supporting real-time data collection."
    DTDFVocab:producedData BuildingPressureDataTransmitted
]

instance StructuralHealthSensor : DTDFVocab:SensingComponent [
    base:desc "Sensor configured by Building Control Engineers within BIM environment to monitor structural integrity metrics (e.g., vibration, strain). Part of the BIM-enriched device modeling process supporting real-time data collection."
    DTDFVocab:producedData StructuralHealthDataTransmitted
]

instance EquipmentStatusSensor : DTDFVocab:SensingComponent [
    base:desc "Sensor configured by Building Control Engineers within BIM environment to monitor operational status of building equipment (e.g., pumps, valves). Part of the BIM-enriched device modeling process supporting real-time data collection."
    DTDFVocab:producedData EquipmentStatusDataTransmitted
]

// C4: Physical-to-virtual interaction
instance BuildingTemperatureDataTransmitted : DTDFVocab:DataTransmitted [
    DTDFVocab:producedFrom BuildingTemperatureSensor
]

instance BuildingHumidityDataTransmitted : DTDFVocab:DataTransmitted [
    DTDFVocab:producedFrom BuildingHumiditySensor
]

instance BuildingPressureDataTransmitted : DTDFVocab:DataTransmitted [
    DTDFVocab:producedFrom BuildingPressureSensor
]

instance StructuralHealthDataTransmitted : DTDFVocab:DataTransmitted [
    DTDFVocab:producedFrom StructuralHealthSensor
]

instance EquipmentStatusDataTransmitted : DTDFVocab:DataTransmitted [
    DTDFVocab:producedFrom EquipmentStatusSensor
]

// C10: Models/Data
instance BimStaticModel : DTDFVocab:Model [
    base:desc "Foundational Building Information Model representing static asset information (geometry, materials, systems) enabling interoperability across AECO workflows. Serves as the primary data source for Digital Twin transformation."
    DTDFVocab:inputTo BimToDtTransformationEnabler
]

instance BimEnrichedModel : DTDFVocab:Model [
    base:desc "Semantically enriched BIM model incorporating device configurations (sensors, actuators, controllers) through Model-Driven Engineering principles. Serves as the unified semantic foundation for Digital Twin artifacts."
    DTDFVocab:inputTo BimToDtTransformationEnabler, RealTimeDataIntegrationEnabler
]

instance OperationalBehavioralModel : DTDFVocab:Model [
    base:desc "Behavioral model representing control logic and operational workflows derived from BIM-enriched device configurations. Enables real-time synchronization between physical and digital systems."
    DTDFVocab:inputTo RealTimeDataIntegrationEnabler
]

instance PerformanceAnalyticalModel : DTDFVocab:Model [
    base:desc "Analytical model for performance metrics and predictive simulations interconnected through semantic graph enabling cross-domain reasoning."
    DTDFVocab:inputTo CustomAnalyticsIntegrationEnabler
]

instance BuildingTemperatureData : DTDFVocab:Data [
    base:desc "Real-time temperature data collected from building systems with preprocessing for validation and normalization before integration into Digital Twin."
    DTDFVocab:fromData BuildingTemperatureDataTransmitted
    DTDFVocab:inputTo RealTimeDataIntegrationEnabler, ImmersiveVisualizationEnabler
]

instance BuildingHumidityData : DTDFVocab:Data [
    base:desc "Real-time humidity data collected from building systems with preprocessing for validation and normalization before integration into Digital Twin."
    DTDFVocab:fromData BuildingHumidityDataTransmitted
    DTDFVocab:inputTo RealTimeDataIntegrationEnabler, CustomAnalyticsIntegrationEnabler
]

instance BuildingPressureData : DTDFVocab:Data [
    base:desc "Real-time pressure data collected from building systems (HVAC, plumbing) with preprocessing for validation and normalization before integration into Digital Twin."
    DTDFVocab:fromData BuildingPressureDataTransmitted
    DTDFVocab:inputTo RealTimeDataIntegrationEnabler, ControlLogicEnabler
]

instance StructuralHealthData : DTDFVocab:Data [
    base:desc "Real-time structural health data collected from building systems with preprocessing for validation and normalization before integration into Digital Twin."
    DTDFVocab:fromData StructuralHealthDataTransmitted
    DTDFVocab:inputTo RealTimeDataIntegrationEnabler
]

instance EquipmentStatusData : DTDFVocab:Data [
    base:desc "Real-time equipment status data collected from building systems with preprocessing for validation and normalization before integration into Digital Twin."
    DTDFVocab:fromData EquipmentStatusDataTransmitted
    DTDFVocab:inputTo RealTimeDataIntegrationEnabler, FacilityManagementEnabler
]

// C11: Enablers
instance BimToDtTransformationEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Model-Driven Engineering framework for transforming static BIM models into operational Digital Twin artifacts with minimal manual intervention."
    DTDFVocab:enables RealTimeMonitoringService, SimulationAnalysisService
]

instance RealTimeDataIntegrationEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Open-source framework leveraging Eclipse Hono and Ditto for scalable, interoperable real-time data exchange between physical and virtual layers."
    DTDFVocab:enables RealTimeMonitoringService, ControlLogicService, LifecycleOptimizationService
]

instance ImmersiveVisualizationEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "High-fidelity visualization engine using Unreal Engine to create rich, interactive 3D representations of physical assets supporting immersive analysis."
    DTDFVocab:enables RichVisualizationService
]

instance CustomAnalyticsIntegrationEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Modular architecture with standardized extension points enabling DT Engineers to develop and integrate custom analytics services."
    DTDFVocab:enables CustomAnalyticsService
]

instance ControlLogicEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Framework supporting definition of control logic and device actuation directly tied to Digital Twin's operational semantics."
    DTDFVocab:enables ControlLogicService, AutomatedDecisionSupportService
]

instance FacilityManagementEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Remote control interfaces integrated into Digital Twin's runtime environment enabling Facility Managers to operate physical infrastructure."
    DTDFVocab:enables FacilityManagementService
]

// C6: Services
instance RealTimeMonitoringService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Continuous observation of physical asset's performance by integrating runtime data with static models for environmental conditions and equipment status."
    DTDFVocab:provides BuildingPerformanceInsight, AnomalyDetectionInsight
]

instance SimulationAnalysisService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Model-driven simulations supporting what-if scenarios and performance evaluations for design validation and operational adjustments."
    DTDFVocab:provides ScenarioEvaluationInsight, DesignValidationInsight
]

instance LifecycleOptimizationService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Data-driven optimization across entire building lifecycle including design, construction, and operational phases."
    DTDFVocab:provides OptimizationRecommendationInsight, CostReductionInsight
]

instance ControlLogicService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Automated decision-support mechanisms adjusting system parameters based on real-time feedback for energy management and structural adjustments."
    DTDFVocab:provides AutomatedAdjustmentAction, EnergyOptimizationAction
]

instance RichVisualizationService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Immersive, user-friendly interfaces visualizing asset states, anomalies, and optimization opportunities using Unreal Engine-compatible rendering."
    DTDFVocab:provides VisualAssetStateInsight, InteractiveAnomalyVisualizationInsight
]

instance CustomAnalyticsService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Domain-specific processing capabilities integrated via standardized extension points for energy optimization and predictive maintenance."
    DTDFVocab:provides CustomAnalyticsInsight
]

instance PredictiveMaintenanceService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Predictive analytics for identifying potential failures and optimizing maintenance schedules based on real-time and historical data."
    DTDFVocab:provides MaintenancePredictionInsight, FailurePreventionAction
]

instance FacilityManagementService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Real-time monitoring and control operations for Facility Managers including HVAC adjustments and alert triggering."
    DTDFVocab:provides FacilityControlInsight, RemoteOperationAction
]

instance AutomatedDecisionSupportService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Automated mechanisms for adjusting system parameters based on real-time feedback and predefined operational semantics."
    DTDFVocab:provides AutomatedParameterAdjustmentAction
]

// C2: Acting Components
instance BuildingHVACActuator : DTDFVocab:ActingComponent [
    base:desc "Actuator component configured by Building Control Engineers within BIM environment for HVAC system control. Enables remote operation via Digital Twin's runtime environment."
]

instance BuildingPlumbingActuator : DTDFVocab:ActingComponent [
    base:desc "Actuator component configured by Building Control Engineers within BIM environment for plumbing system control. Enables remote operation via Digital Twin's runtime environment."
]

instance StructuralAdjustmentActuator : DTDFVocab:ActingComponent [
    base:desc "Actuator component configured by Building Control Engineers within BIM environment for structural adjustment systems. Enables remote operation via Digital Twin's runtime environment with safety constraints."
]

// C17: Insights/Actions
instance BuildingPerformanceInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Real-time correlation of operational data with semantically enriched BIM model to identify building performance metrics and operational efficiency."
]

instance AnomalyDetectionInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Identification of deviations from expected operational parameters through real-time data analysis and visualization."
]

instance ScenarioEvaluationInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Evaluation of potential design or operational changes through model-driven simulations before physical implementation."
]

instance DesignValidationInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Validation of design decisions against real-time performance data to ensure compliance with operational requirements."
]

instance OptimizationRecommendationInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Data-driven recommendations for improving building performance across lifecycle stages including energy efficiency and structural integrity."
]

instance CostReductionInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Identification of cost-saving opportunities through operational optimization and predictive maintenance strategies."
]

instance VisualAssetStateInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Immersive visualization of current asset states including geometric representations and real-time operational data overlays."
]

instance InteractiveAnomalyVisualizationInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Interactive 3D visualization of detected anomalies with contextual data for Facility Managers to investigate issues."
]

instance CustomAnalyticsInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Domain-specific analytical results generated by custom services integrated via standardized extension points."
]

instance MaintenancePredictionInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Predictive analysis of equipment health to forecast maintenance requirements and prevent failures."
]

instance FacilityControlInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Real-time operational status of building systems presented through immersive interfaces for Facility Managers."
]

instance AutomatedAdjustmentAction : DTDFVocab:Action [
    base:desc "Automated adjustment of system parameters based on real-time feedback and predefined control logic."
    DTDFVocab:IsAutomatic true
]

instance EnergyOptimizationAction : DTDFVocab:Action [
    base:desc "Automated optimization of energy consumption through HVAC and lighting system adjustments."
    DTDFVocab:IsAutomatic true
]

instance FailurePreventionAction : DTDFVocab:Action [
    base:desc "Automated triggering of maintenance actions based on predictive maintenance insights."
    DTDFVocab:IsAutomatic true
]

instance RemoteOperationAction : DTDFVocab:Action [
    base:desc "Remote control of building systems by Facility Managers through Digital Twin interfaces."
    DTDFVocab:IsAutomatic false
]

instance AutomatedParameterAdjustmentAction : DTDFVocab:Action [
    base:desc "Automated adjustment of system parameters based on real-time feedback and operational semantics."
    DTDFVocab:IsAutomatic true
]

instance OptimizationRecommendationAction : DTDFVocab:Action [
    base:desc "Implementation of optimization recommendations derived from lifecycle analysis."
    DTDFVocab:IsAutomatic false
]

instance virtual_to_physical_interaction : DTDFVocab:VirtualToPhysical [
    base:desc "The DT system enables control flows from the digital twin to physical infrastructure via **runtime configuration management**, allowing Facility Managers to issue commands for real-time monitoring and operational adjustments. While the document does not specify exact command types (e.g., HVAC adjustments, lighting controls) or control message formats, the framework supports bidirectional validation and feedback systems to ensure command integrity. Conflict resolution is implicitly managed through the DT Framework’s centralized coordination, though explicit mechanisms (e.g., priority-based arbitration, rollback protocols) are not described. Command execution confirmation is facilitated by the system’s real-time synchronization, where physical responses (e.g., sensor feedback) are looped back to the DT for validation. Authentication and authorization are addressed under non-functional requirements (NF_X), ensuring secure access for authorized roles (e.g., Building Control Engineers, DT Engineers), but specific protocols (e.g., OAuth2, TLS) are not mentioned."
]

instance twinning_time_scale : DTDFVocab:TimeScale [
    base:desc "The Digital Twin system enforces **real-time data exchange capabilities** to ensure **continuous synchronization** between physical buildings and their digital counterparts, enabling instantaneous bidirectional updates. The framework supports **dynamic operational needs** by aligning with the AECO (Architecture, Engineering, Construction, and Operations) domain, where static BIM (Building Information Modeling) artifacts are transformed into runtime-capable representations. While explicit synchronization frequencies (e.g., sub-second, millisecond-level, or design-phase granularity) are not specified, the emphasis on **real-time** implies low-latency requirements for operational monitoring and control. The system prioritizes **temporal alignment** between physical and digital components to reflect real-world conditions without explicit mention of granularity thresholds for non-critical systems (e.g., security or maintenance)."
]

instance dt_constellation : DTDFVocab:Constellation [
    base:desc "The Digital Twin system employs a **coordinated architecture pattern** centered around a **DT Framework** acting as a **central hub** for bidirectional data exchange and system-wide orchestration. Key components include:
  - **Role-based orchestration**: The framework integrates contributions from **Building Control Engineers** (device modeling), **Facility Managers** (real-time monitoring), and **DT Engineers** (service extension), ensuring aligned responsibilities across the Digital Twin life cycle.
  - **Component integration**: The modular design with **standardized extension points** allows for plug-and-play integration of custom services and analytics, enabling **runtime configuration management** to adapt to evolving operational requirements without full redeployment.
  - **Resource management**: The system prioritizes **scalability** (from individual components to entire infrastructure systems) and **maintainability** (low-overhead updates), while addressing **interoperability** across heterogeneous systems via non-functional requirements (NF_X). The architecture emphasizes **dynamic adaptability**, bridging static BIM representations with real-time operational needs through a **systematic requirements-driven approach**."
]

instance life_cycle_stages : DTDFVocab:EvolutionStage [
    base:desc "The Digital Twin (DT) lifecycle in the proposed model-driven deployment framework spans from **initial device modeling** to **runtime operation**, addressing the gap between static Building Information Modeling (BIM) representations and dynamic DT requirements. Key phases include:
  1. **Device Modeling and Configuration**: Building Control Engineers define sensors, actuators, and controllers directly within the BIM environment, enriching static BIM models with Building Control System (BCS) components to create a **unified semantic foundation** for subsequent transformations.
  2. **Model Transformation and Artifact Generation**: Leveraging **Model-Driven Engineering (MDE) principles**, the framework extracts structured representations from enriched BIM models and **automatically generates deployable DT artifacts** (e.g., simulation models, control logic, or service definitions) with minimal manual intervention.
  3. **DT Deployment and Synchronization**: The framework ensures **real-time data exchange** between physical buildings and their digital twins, maintaining continuous synchronization via bidirectional communication protocols (not explicitly specified but implied for dynamic alignment).
  4. **Runtime Operation and Customization**: The DT operates in tandem with physical infrastructure, enabling Facility Managers to monitor system states and interact with the twin. **Modular architecture** with standardized extension points supports integration of **custom services and analytics** (e.g., plugins or third-party tools) to extend functionality dynamically.
  Transition management between phases is governed by **automated workflows** tied to MDE principles, ensuring seamless progression from static BIM to dynamic DT representations. Governance is implicit through role-based access (e.g., Building Control Engineers, Facility Managers, DT Engineers) and **modular validation** of generated artifacts before deployment."
]

instance fidelity_and_validity_considerations : DTDFVocab:FidelityConsideration [
    base:desc "The Digital Twin system addresses **model fidelity** through **BIM-derived representations** and **runtime synchronization**, ensuring alignment between physical and digital states. **Validation and verification** are partially addressed via the **Overall Digital Twin Entanglement (ODTE) metric**, which evaluates the **entanglement** (i.e., the degree of synchronization and interdependence) of the resulting DT. The framework implicitly supports **uncertainty quantification** through **model-driven transformations**, where discrepancies between BIM’s static representations and the DT’s dynamic requirements are mitigated via **automated artifact generation**. Error detection and correction mechanisms are not explicitly detailed, but the **modular architecture** allows for **custom services** to be integrated for **quality assurance**. No specific **error thresholds**, **standards compliance** (e.g., ISO 19650), or **formal verification methods** are mentioned."
]

instance dt_technical_connection : DTDFVocab:TechnicalConnection [
    base:desc "The DT system’s technical network infrastructure relies on a **modular architecture** with standardized extension points, enabling integration of custom services and analytics. Real-time data exchange is achieved using **Eclipse Hono** (for IoT data ingestion) and **Ditto** (for digital twin state management), ensuring interoperability across heterogeneous systems. The network topology is not explicitly detailed, but the framework’s design supports scalability from individual components to entire infrastructure systems, with non-functional requirements (NF_X) addressing bandwidth, latency, and reliability. Redundancy mechanisms are implied through runtime configuration management, allowing dynamic adjustments without full redeployment. Security protocols for network communication are not specified, though the system’s interoperability focus suggests adherence to industry standards (e.g., OPC UA, MQTT) for secure data transmission."
]

instance dt_hosting_deployment : DTDFVocab:Deployment [
    base:desc "The DT system’s deployment infrastructure is underpinned by a **modular architecture** with **runtime configuration management**, enabling adjustments without full redeployment. While the document does not specify hosting platforms (e.g., cloud, edge, on-premise) or computational/storage requirements, the **non-functional requirements (NF_X)** highlight **scalability** (from individual components to entire infrastructure systems) and **maintainability** (low-overhead updates). The framework supports **deployment models** tailored to the AECO domain, where *Building Control Engineers* initiate deployment via BIM tools, and *DT Engineers* extend capabilities through service integration. Availability and reliability are implicitly addressed through the **systematic requirements-driven approach**, though specifics like distributed storage or failover mechanisms are not provided. The DT Framework acts as a **central hub**, facilitating seamless transitions from enriched BIM models to operational DTs throughout the building life cycle."
]

instance horizontal_integration : DTDFVocab:HoriIntegration [
    base:desc "The Digital Twin framework ensures **horizontal integration** with external systems through:
  - **Data exchange protocols**: Bidirectional synchronization between physical buildings (e.g., IoT sensors, building automation systems) and their digital counterparts, leveraging **standardized extension points** for interoperability.
  - **Interoperability standards**: Compliance with **BIM tools** (used by Building Control Engineers for device modeling) and enterprise systems (e.g., facility management software), ensuring seamless data flow across heterogeneous environments.
  - **Integration patterns**: The framework acts as a **central hub** for coordinating interactions between Digital Twins and external systems, supporting dependencies such as real-time monitoring (Facility Managers) and custom service extensions (DT Engineers). The **modular architecture** enables integration with other Digital Twins or enterprise systems via well-defined interfaces, while **runtime configuration management** allows for adaptive adjustments without disrupting existing workflows."
]

instance standardization : DTDFVocab:Standardization [
    base:desc "The framework adheres to **two primary standardization pillars**:
  1. **Building Information Modeling (BIM)**: Serves as the **foundational data model** for DT deployment, providing **static representations** of building assets. However, the framework **extends BIM’s capabilities** by enriching it with **dynamic BCS components** (sensors, actuators, controllers) to support DT requirements. This approach ensures **interoperability with existing BIM tools** (e.g., Autodesk Revit, ArchiCAD) while addressing BIM’s **inherent limitations** in representing real-time systems.
  2. **Eclipse IoT Tools**:
     - **Eclipse Hono**: Integrated for **secure, lightweight messaging** between DT components and physical devices, enabling **scalable data exchange** in constrained environments.
     - **Eclipse Ditto**: Used for **digital twin representation and management**, providing **device abstraction layers** and **state management** for synchronized twins.
  **No explicit mention** is made of the following standards or protocols in the provided documents:
  - **MQTT/AMQP** (not referenced, though Eclipse Hono may imply MQTT-like functionality).
  - **OMG MDA (Model-Driven Architecture)** (MDE is used, but not explicitly tied to OMG standards).
  - **IEC 62541 (OPC UA)** or **ISO 23226** (not cited).
  - **BaSyx** (mentioned only as related work, not as an adopted interoperability standard).
  **Interoperability** is achieved through:
  - **Semantic Alignment**: Enriched BIM models act as a **unified semantic layer**, ensuring consistency between physical and digital representations.
  - **Modular Architecture**: Standardized **extension points** allow integration of **third-party services** (e.g., analytics, control systems) without proprietary lock-in.
  The framework does not specify **certification requirements** or **compliance frameworks** (e.g., ISO 19650 for BIM), but its **model-driven approach** and **tool integrations** (Eclipse Hono/Ditto) suggest alignment with **IoT and digital twin best practices** in the building automation domain."
]